side of 109th Street.

P. L. Sperr.

715973f-a.title: Manhattan: Amsterdam Avenue - Cathedral Parkway
715973f-a.text:
Amsterdam Avenue, at the N. E. corner of Cathedral Parkway
(West 110th Street), showing the Leake : Watts Orphan Asylum.
Incorporated in 1831 by John G. Leake and Bobert Watts; the
buildings here were erected in 1843 at 113th Street. After
the sale of the site to the Protestant Episcopal Archdioscese
for the site of St. John's Cathedral in 1886, they moved to
Ludlow. For further details, see, Kings Handbook of New York
(1893), page 430.
1892
H. N. Tiemann, photo
Gift of Urbrock Collection
